1) IO map

Inputs (digital)

I0.0 — Start / Run (system enable)

I0.1 — NS vehicle detector (optional)

I0.2 — EW vehicle detector (optional)

I0.3 — Pedestrian NS request (push button)

I0.4 — Pedestrian EW request (push button)

I0.5 — Manual override / Fault reset (optional)

Outputs (digital)

Q0.0 — NS Green

Q0.1 — NS Yellow

Q0.2 — NS Red

Q0.3 — EW Green

Q0.4 — EW Yellow

Q0.5 — EW Red

Q0.6 — Pedestrian NS Walk

Q0.7 — Pedestrian EW Walk

Internal memory / timers

T_NS_Green — Timer for NS green

T_NS_Yellow — Timer for NS yellow

T_All_Red — Timer for all-red

T_EW_Green, T_EW_Yellow

Bit: STATE_0..STATE_3 or an integer STATE (0..3)

State encoding (recommended)

STATE = 0 → NS Green

STATE = 1 → NS Yellow

STATE = 2 → All Red (transition)

STATE = 3 → EW Green

STATE = 4 → EW Yellow

STATE = 5 → All Red (transition back)
